Package: cephsumfs
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: libcrc32c1
Description: External checksum helper for XRootD on Ceph-backed POSIX storage
 cephsumfs computes and caches file checksums for XRootD using Linux extended
 attributes in the XrdCks wire format. It supports adler32, crc32, crc32c,
 md5, and sha256, and is designed to be called by XRootD as an external
 checksum helper via the xrd.chksum directive.
 .
 Checksums are read from an xattr cache when available and validated against
 the file mtime before use. Stale or absent entries are recomputed and written
 back automatically. File reads use a multithreaded os.pread() pipeline to
 hide per-read latency on networked CephFS storage.
